# Frontend conventions

## Architecture

Single `public/index.html` contains structure, styles, card deck, and logic. Supporting scripts in `public/js/`.

## Card schema

```javascript
{ id, category, type: "question"|"action", depth: 1-3, question? | action? }
```

- IDs: unique positive integers, sequential when adding new cards
- Categories: must exist in `categoryThemes` for correct theming
- `depth` renders as heart icons (1–3)

## UI patterns

- Category sidebar filters deck via `getDeckForCategory()`
- CSS variables in `:root`; per-category overrides via `applyCategoryTheme()`
- Modal for answering questions; actions skip the text input
- Room code shown in header; copy button shares `?room=CODE` URL

## Ads

- Config: `public/js/ads-config.js` (`CONNECTION_CARDS_ADS`)
- Loader: `public/js/adsense.js`
- Do not enable ads without valid `publisherId` and slot IDs

## Avoid

- Adding npm/bundler tooling without explicit request
- Splitting `index.html` into modules unless asked
- Breaking the RTDB listener in `initFirebase()` — it drives all UI state
